{
  "texts": [
    "MAD-DAG provides the most robust defense available.",
    "A Calculating the Average Number of Whale Transactions per BlockAssuming all miners are honest, it means that whenever a new block is created, it includes a whale transaction if one is available and that the new block is immediately published and accepted by everyone else.",
    "Also, recall that when the number of whale transactions is max_pool, any excess transactions are discarded.The number of whale transactions follows a Markov chain with states 0, 1,..., max_pool.",
    "For 1 < 𝑖 < max_pool, the probability to move right (the number of transactions increases by 1) is 𝛿 1+𝛿 and the probability to move left (the number of transactions decreases by 1) is 1 1+𝛿 (this matches the ratio 𝛿 that our model stipulates).",
    "For 𝑖 = 0, the probability to move right is 𝛿 1+𝛿 and the probability to stay is 1 1+𝛿."
  ]
}